title: The Complete Tommy Dorsey Vol. II (1936) Bluebird 24/96 vinyl
description:
TOMMY DORSEY - THE COMLETE TOMMY DORSEY VOLUME II / 1936

24/96 mono VINYL rip with SCANS

SIDE A:

1. Gotta Go To Work Again (vocal - The Three Esquires)
2. A Little Rendezvous In Honolulu (vocal - Jack Leonard)
3. That Lovely Night In Budapest (vocal - Jack Leonard)
4. Every Minute of the Hour of The Day (vocal - Edythe Wright)

Recorded 2/3/36 New York: Tommy Dorsey (tb), Andy Ferretti, Sterling Bose, Joe Bauer (tp), Ben Pickering, Joe Ortolano (tb), Noni Bernardi, Tommy Mace (as), Clyde Rounds, Sid Block (ts), Dick Jones (p), Mac Cheikes (g), Gene Traxler (b), Sammy Weiss (d)

5. You (vocal - Edythe Wright)
6. Robins And Roses (vocal - Edythe Wright)
7. You Never Looked So Beautiful
8. You Started Me dreaming (vocal - Joe Dixon)

Recorded 3/25/36 New York: Tommy Dorsey (tb), Sam Skolnick, Max Kaminsky Joe Bauer (tp), Ben Pickering, Walter Mercurio (tb), Fred Stulce, Joe Dixon (as), Clyde Rounds, Sid Block (ts), Dick Jones, (p), William Schaffer (g), Gene Traxler (b), Dave Tough (d)

SIDE B:

1. It's You I'm Talkin' About (vocal - Edythe Wright)
2. Will I Ever Know It (vocal - Edythe Wright)
3. Rhythm Saved The World (vocal - Edythe Wright)

Recorded 3/27/37 New York: same as above

4. Stardust (vocal - Edythe Wright)
5. Royal Garden Blues

Recorded 4/3/36 New York: Same as above except Bud Freeman, Bob Bunch (ts) replace Rounds, Block

6. Jada
7. At the Codfish Ball (vocal - Edythe Wright)

Recorded 4/15/36 New York: same as above

8. Where is My Heart (vocal - Jack Leonard)

SIDE C:

1. Long Ago And Far Away (vocal - Jack Leonard)
2. Mary Had A Little Lamb (vocal - Edythe Wright)
3. Did I Remember (vocal - Edythe Wright)

Recorded 5/20/36 New York: same as above except Red Bone (tb) replaces Mercurio, Clyde Rounds (as) replces Stulce

4. You've Gotta Eat Your Spinach Baby (vocal - Edythe Wright)
5. On The Beach At Bali Bali (vocal - Edythe Wright)
6. No Regret (vocal Jack Leonard)
7. San Francisco (vocal - Edythe Wright)
8. That's A Plenty

Recorded 6/9/36 New York: Walter Mercurio (tb) replaces Bone, Carmen Mastren (g) replaces Schaffer

9. After You've Gone

SIDE D:

1. For Sentimental Reasons (vocal - Jack Leonard)
2. Head Over Heels In Love (vocal - Edythe Wright)
3. High Hat, A Piccolo And A Cane (vocal - Three Esquires)
4. Close To Me (vocal - Jack Leonard)
5. May I Have The Next Romance With You (vocal - Jack Leonard)
6. Sleep
7. Another Perfect Night Is Ending (vocal - Jack Leonard)
8. Maple Leaf Rag

Recorded 10/18/36 New York: Steve Lipkins (tp) replaces Skolnick, Les Jenkins (tb) replaces Pickering

1977 Bluebird/RCA
